—Es un caso de necesidad —dijo Egbert—. Cuando una nutria empieza con cosas de esta clase, ya no para.~"It's a case of necessity," said Egbert; "once an otter takes to that sort of thing it won't stop."  
—Puede que se vaya a otra parte, ahora que ya no quedan gallinas —sugirió Amanda.~"Perhaps it will go elsewhere now there are no more fowls left," suggested Amanda.  
—Casi se diría que quieres proteger a esa bestia —dijo Egbert.~"One would think you wanted to shield the beast," said Egbert.  
